        <h3 class="GuideHeading text-start pt-1">Factors to Consider When Selecting Jewelry Materials</h3>


        <ul class="pt-2">
            <li><strong>Durability:</strong> Platinum is the best for daily wear however it is richer than silver or gold which is comparatively softer.</li><br>
            <li><strong>Allergies:</strong> If you have an allergy to most metals, buy only the safe items such as gold that do not contain nickel or wear platinum.</li><br>
            <li><strong>Metal Color:</strong> Pay attention to how the metal works with gemstones or diamonds. For instance, yellow gold will look much better with yellowish colored stones, while with white or silver metals such stones will look pale and dull.</li><br>
            <li><strong>Budget:</strong> Ideal for the pocket friendly is silver and 14K gold, luxury available for up to 1K platinum and 18K gold.</li><br>
        </ul>
        
    </div>
</section>


